latestPosts.caption:
Inspired by the Camille corset first seen in the Vivienne Westwood Harris Tweed collection, the Grand Camille is finished with a full skirt and overlapping front pleats.⁠
⁠
The gown is styled with the Rita bodice, offering a fitted silhouette and delicate lace detailing. The design features long sleeves and a Victorian-inspired high neck complete with a row of covered buttons, fastening the back.⁠
⁠
#VWBridal #WestwoodBridal

The exaggerated, asymmetrical tiered skirt features a train at the back of the gown, for an added air of opulence.⁠

To close her headline performance at Glastonbury Festival 2025, @Doechii appeared in a custom ensemble inspired by the iconic Spring-Summer 1994 ‘Café Society’ collection.⁠
⁠
Adding further energy to the stand-out performance, Doechii’s dancers and DJ Milan wore full Vivienne Westwood looks.⁠
⁠
Styling: @sam__woolf

latestPosts.caption:
Artist @Doechii wore custom Vivienne Westwood for her outstanding headline performance at Glastonbury Festival 2025.⁠
⁠
Her looks transformed to reveal a bralette and matching custom ultra mini skirt in blue striped wool – a look first seen on the runway for the Vivienne Westwood Spring-Summer 1994 show titled, ‘Café Society’ – worn with a custom-made pair of gold crystal embellished Vivienne Westwood orb motif nipple pasties.⁠
⁠
Styling: @sam__woolf
